Product: Rare Beauty Liquid Touch Weightless Foundation
Price: $30
Review: I can safely say I have almost tried all the foundations popular brands have to offer primarily because I am always up for trying and reviewing new make up products and finding the best in each category. 

Okay so here is my take on this one! The formula is very liquidy, start with a drop and then build it up gradually depending on how much coverage you would prefer. The approach is â€˜less is moreâ€™. This foundation works best for those who have balanced skin. A few extra steps will be needed for those with oily or dry skin. Oily skin users will need a primer that controls oil and a face/setting powder is a must post application while the dry skin users need to moisturize really really well. 

The result after using this foundation was an air brushed and natural looking skin. However, If you have pores or dark spots you may need to build up the coverage or opt for a concealer. Another interesting thing is that the foundation has an applicator instead of a pump which may or may not matter to you but for me pump works better. This foundation may not be the best of the ones I have tried but it can be a good everyday use option. It doesnâ€™t beat the finish I get from Dior Foreever Skin Glow or Armani Luminous Silk Perfect Glow who are in the same light buildable category. 
So i will rate this foundation a 7/10
I definitely liked Rare Beauty Liquid Blush much better.

How do the charlottetilbury & rarebeauty highlighter formulas compare? From wearing these formulas so often and interchangeably, here is what Iâ€™ve gathered: 

Texture: in my own words, the CT formula has more of that soft powdery feel to the touch whereas RB has a smooth silky touch. CT describes her formula as a â€œsatinâ€ texture whereas RB describes her formula as a â€œglass-like sheenâ€ and that is 100% accurate and the best way to describe each individually.

Color: in my swatch photos, we have Champagne Glow from CT (top) & Exhilarate from RB (bottom). You can clearly see that the tone of Exhilarate is far more golden than Champagne Glow which has a true champagne undertone. However, I find on the face I cannot tell a difference.

The number one most asked question I have gotten recently is â€œwhich one is your favorite and the one you recommend?â€ I honestly cannot choose because I love them both so much ğŸ˜† but in all seriousness, do you NEED both? No. I would say it depends on what you like in a glow and how much you are wanting to spend. If you like more of a lit from within glow than go with the CT because of that satin texture but if you prefer something more intense than RB is the way to go.

The RB retails for $25 USD ($8.92/gram)

â–¶ï¸ Today I'll give an impression of these 3 releases from Jardin de Parfums. I'll be giving away a bottle of 23 Voyage later this week, so stay tuned for that if you're interested!

1ï¸âƒ£ 23 VOYAGE is my favorite and the one I'd recommend blindly the most of these, so it was a good pick for the giveaway. I'd describe it as an aromatic amber/vanilla with woody touches. A bright citrussy top, instantly followed by vanilla. There's a hint of sharpness and a slightly green aromatic feeling. Some acidity lasts, but it rather quickly becomes a straight-up sweet and easy to wear vanilla drydown with a dry paper-esque woody tinge. It's cozy, but it lasts well.

2ï¸âƒ£ ORACLE starts off as the most interesting and unique one, as its essentially a coconut scent. It's been compared to Black Orchid, but Oracle is brighter and lighter, easier to wear. This one opens slightly fruity, fig-like and definitely has that signature Black Orchid tinge at first, but transitions into more of a lactonic coconut, sun-tan territory. I really like the opening, but the fruity sweetness gets a bit cloying in the drydown for me.

3ï¸âƒ£ PAPAVERO NERO is a rose-oud that won't surprise most of you. It smells good (probably better than the other two quality-wise to me), but it's been done before. It's a cleaner, saffrony-leather hidden underneath a rose that becomes a tad soapy, with a conventional, safe oud, making it accessible. Nero is being compared to Roja's Amber Aoud, but don't expect that kind of quality here.

âºï¸ In general, I was happy with the scents, but quality-wise they leave something to be desired. As do the caps, the atomizers. The bottles look good (and the unboxing is beautiful actually), but it's not quite there in the details.

Price-wise they're solid and the scent profiles of 23 Voyage and Oracle are interesting, but the fragrances have a generic 'straight from an affordable factory' feeling to them in my opinion. As a self-certified niche snob, they didn't fully appeal to me. I know that a lot of people will feel differently though, so you'll have to try for yourself... or win this week's giveaway of course.

ğŸ’vievemuse Shimmer Eye Wand (Old Gold) and Modern Matte Lipstick (Lara). I didn't use them much in 12 months (less than 10X). The wand is cute but I always forget about it. I like the shade of the pstick but I am not a fan of the formula (too drying for my liking)

ğŸ’narsissist Climax palette. The palette that started my love for greens. I went back and forth for months on this palette, but luckly I got her before it was too late

ğŸ’lysbeautyofficial Higher Standard Satin Matte Cream Blush (Confident and Kindness) and Aim High Pressed Powder Highlighter (Genuine). While I adored the blushes (the formula is included in my top of 2022), I quite disliked the highlighter. 

ğŸ’rarebeauty Soft Pinch Liquid Blush (Love) and Positive Light Liquid Luminizer (Mesmerize). I used the highlighter a lot, while the blush didn't get enough love. I really like the formula, but the shade is actually pretty similar to Confident and I prefer Lys blushes (they are easier to use IMO)

ğŸ’sephoracollection Colorful Eyeshadows (First Light and Ultraviolet). While I used First Light a lot, Ultraviolet was forgotten. It is beautiful but It's not a shade a tend to use on everyday base (and that's reminds me that I don't need the new CT pop shot if I didn't use this enough)

farmacybeauty Filling Good - This didn't work out. It foamed up almost every time I used it and has a pretty strong scent that smelt a little off. 

beekman1802 MilkShake Toner - 10 out of 10 I will always have this. It tones, hydrates, and plumps all in one step. I use it almost every day!

selflessbyhyram launched in June 2021 with sephora as its exclusive retail partner. The global retailer unceremoniously dumped it after only 18 months on the shelves. When this news broke, we assumed Selfless was on its way to the place where influencer and celebrity brands go to die.

But Gen-Z skin-fluencer hyram Yarbro refused to be broken and tossed aside by Sephora's notoriously fickle (and often misguided) marketers and merchandisers.

Selfless by Hyram, in a bold post-Sephora pivot, is moving to target - and lowering its product prices.

Yarbro, who has 6.5 million followers on TikTok, 4.55 million on YouTube, and 976,000 on Instagram, has always recommended "drugstore" skincare on his social platforms because that's where the majority of his followers shop. 

The new online and in-store partnership with Target (beginning February 5th) retails the formerly $16-$30 products for only $13-$24. Much more in line with Mass-market skincare brands like larocheposay, neutrogena, olay, and L'Oreal Revitalift. It also gives the brand additional exposure in the over 300 ultabeauty "Target" shop-in-shops, alongside naturiumskin, founded by fellow skin-fluencer susanyara.

Regarding the company's state, Yarbo said in an interview, "We're still charging full speed ahead...Target represents what I've always wanted the brand to be, which is more accessible." 

What do you think about this move? 
Will it save Selfless by Hyram?

I am 44 years old and my skin has never looked better!
